## 2. InstancedMesh Patterns

### Core Benefits

InstancedMesh reduces draw calls from N (one per object) to 1, significantly improving WebGL performance.

**Performance envelope:**
- **Optimal:** 1,000 - 100,000 instances
- **MMS target:** ~60,000 tasks
- **Desktop performance:** Excellent
- **Mobile caveat:** May actually be slower than naive rendering on low-end devices (Quest 2 example: 85fps naive vs 55fps instanced at 2600 instances)

**Source:** [Three.js Forum - When is InstancedMesh worth it](https://discourse.threejs.org/t/when-is-instancedmesh-worth-it-in-three/62044)

### Creation and Updates

```typescript
// Create InstancedMesh
const mesh = new THREE.InstancedMesh(geometry, material, count);

// Update transform for instance i
const matrix = new THREE.Matrix4();
matrix.compose(position, quaternion, scale);
mesh.setMatrixAt(i, matrix);
mesh.instanceMatrix.needsUpdate = true; // CRITICAL: Mark for GPU update

// Update color for instance i
mesh.setColorAt(i, color);
mesh.instanceColor!.needsUpdate = true; // CRITICAL
```

**Source:** [Three.js InstancedMesh Docs](https://threejs.org/docs/pages/InstancedMesh.html)

### Attribute Buffers Best Practices

1. **Always set `needsUpdate = true`** after modifying `instanceMatrix` or `instanceColor`
2. **Compute bounding box manually** - not auto-calculated, call after transforms
3. **Use `count` property** to hide instances dynamically (set lower than allocated)
4. **Pre-allocate** to maximum needed count to avoid recreating mesh

### Color Management

```typescript
// Set per-instance colors
const color = new THREE.Color();
for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
  color.setHex(getColorForInstance(i));
  mesh.setColorAt(i, color);
}
mesh.instanceColor!.needsUpdate = true;
```

### Performance Limits and Optimization

| Technique | Benefit | When to Use |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| **LOD with multiple InstancedMesh** | ~2x FPS improvement | Complex geometries |
| **Per-instance frustum culling** | Skip off-screen instances | Scattered world-space data |
| **BVH spatial index** | Fast culling + raycasting | Mostly static instances |
| **Custom sorting for transparency** | Correct render order | Transparent materials |

**Source:** [VR Me Up - InstancedMesh Performance Optimizations](https://vrmeup.com/devlog/devlog_10_threejs_instancedmesh_performance_optimizations.html)

### Enhanced Libraries

**@three.ez/instanced-mesh** (InstancedMesh2):
- Dynamic instance addition
- Object3D-like instances with transforms
- Built-in per-instance frustum culling
- BVH support for raycasting

**Recommendation:** Consider for future if frustum culling becomes a bottleneck.

**Source:** [npm - @three.ez/instanced-mesh](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@three.ez/instanced-mesh)

### Resource Cleanup

```typescript
// CRITICAL: Dispose on unmount to free GPU memory
useEffect(() => {
  return () => {
    mesh.dispose();
    geometry.dispose();
    material.dispose();
  };
}, []);
```

