## 3. deck.gl Comparison

### deck.gl Overview

deck.gl is a WebGL2/WebGPU visualization framework optimized for large-scale data visualization.

**Performance envelope:**
- ~1M data items at 60 FPS on 2015 MacBook Pro
- Performance degrades significantly approaching 10M items
- Browser memory limits practical usage to 10M-100M without chunking

**Source:** [deck.gl Performance Optimization](https://deck.gl/docs/developer-guide/performance)

### OrthographicView for 2D

OrthographicView is designed for non-geospatial 2D visualization:

```javascript
import { OrthographicView } from '@deck.gl/core';

const view = new OrthographicView({
  controller: true,
  flipY: true // top-left coordinates
});

// View state
const viewState = {
  target: [0, 0, 0],
  zoom: 1,
  minZoom: -2,
  maxZoom: 10
};
```

**Source:** [deck.gl OrthographicView](https://deck.gl/docs/api-reference/core/orthographic-view)

### Pros vs R3F for MMS

| Aspect | deck.gl | React Three Fiber |
|--------|---------|-------------------|
| **2D Timeline** | Designed for this | Requires workarounds |
| **Data binding** | Excellent (layer props) | Manual attribute updates |
| **64-bit projection** | Built-in | Manual |
| **Picking** | Built-in (16M items/layer) | Manual raycasting |
| **React integration** | Fair (@deck.gl/react) | Excellent (native renderer) |
| **3D capabilities** | Limited | Excellent |
| **Learning curve** | Moderate | Lower (Three.js knowledge) |
| **LOD transitions** | Layer visibility | Manual implementation |

### Cons vs R3F for MMS

1. **Migration cost:** Existing R3F implementation is working
2. **Less flexible:** deck.gl layers have fixed capabilities
3. **Shader customization:** Harder than Three.js ShaderMaterial
4. **Community size:** Smaller than Three.js ecosystem

### deck.gl Layer Performance Tips

```javascript
// Use typed arrays for performance
const data = {
  length: 60000,
  attributes: {
    getPosition: new Float32Array(/* ... */),
    getColor: new Uint8Array(/* ... */)
  }
};

// Use visibility instead of removing layers
